data.description: ***OPEN HOUSE, Sunday, Feb. 4th, 2-4.*** This charming home is in a USDA eligible area, which means $0 down if you qualify!! With just over 2000 square feet, it’s the perfect combination of space and hominess. The cozy living room has a wood burning fireplace that adds a touch of warmth and character. The formal dining area is perfect for hosting family gatherings or enjoying intimate dinners with loved ones. Cooking will be so enjoyable in this kitchen that boasts updated painted cabinets and a stylish island with a butcher block countertop. The eat in area in the kitchen makes the space perfect for casual meals and also socializing, but one of the best features of the entire house is the fabulous pantry with huge barn doors that provide functionality and a touch of rustic charm. The bedrooms are all generously sized, offering ample room for relaxation and personalization. The primary bath is a sanctuary with a double vanity and a convenient walk in shower. Off the living room, you’ll discover a large screened in porch—an ideal spot to enjoy the outdoors while maintaining comfort and privacy. The unfinished basement, spanning 950 square feet, holds incredible potential for customization and expansion. DIY enthusiasts will appreciate the included workshop, ready for creative projects and hobbies. The backyard is a haven for entertainment, featuring a wood deck that’s perfect for hosting gatherings. Additionally, an urban garden allows you to embrace the joy of growing your own vegetables. Practical updates enhancing the value of this home include a brand new water heater, plus a less than 2 year old roof and HVAC system, per the seller. This ensures peace of mind for the lucky new owners! Don’t miss the opportunity to make 3250 Brackett Dr. your new home. Call your favorite realtor today to schedule a showing and experience the perfect blend of modern living and timeless charm.
